    "Body": " BlockFi's mission is to provide liquidity, transparency and efficiency to digital financial markets by creating products that meet the needs of consumers and corporations across the globe. We build bridges between traditional finance and digital markets that enable growth for all participants. This position provides a large opportunity for professional growth as we scale our organization. The individual who joins our team should expect to scale with our company and be ready to take on larger responsibilities over time. The position will report directly to our Director of Institutional Client Relations. Qualified applicants should respond with a brief intro to their background. Responsibilities Act as point of contact for BlockFi's top tier client base Facilitate bespoke client offerings to assist the institutional team with meeting borrowing/lending demands Proactively engage with private client base to understand their unique needs and provide advice on products and services Drive revenue by structuring loans to fit the needs of the client Opportunity to develop the private client offering into its own market segmentation Attend crypto events in NYC, and potentially outside NYC, to spread the word about BlockFi and source potential clients Source potential clients through social media and our customer support platforms (chat box, reddit, twitter, telegram) Qualifications 2-5 years of industry experience in a customer-facing role Entrepreneurial mindset An understanding of blockchain technology and crypto assets Eagerness to learn and help BlockFi scale Experience with sales The ability to network and build relationships Excellent interpersonal and communication skills Excited to work in an early-stage company and have a high impact on the future of the company's growth Why BlockFi? BlockFi has experienced incredible growth since our launch in August 2017. From raising over $75MM in debt and equity capital to helping thousands of clients (and growing!) do more with their crypto assets, we have established a dominant position as the debt and credit crypto market leader in the US. As we expand our product suite and geographic footprint, our addressable market will grow exponentially. BlockFi's leadership team has decades of experience in the traditional financial services and banking world, and we take a conservative approach to regulation that will position us well for sustainable long-term growth and expansion. In Addition Our team is comprised of highly motivated professionals from diverse backgrounds. We are aiming to become the leading lender in crypto and are poised to redefine the global financial ecosystem for the better. BlockFi is one of the first companies to ever offer crypto-backed loans and the only company whose founding team has an institutional understanding of the debt capital markets and regulatory landscape in the U.S. $48 MM of Series A and B funding led by Valar Ventures with participation from Susquehanna, Winklevoss Capital, Fidelity, Galaxy Digital, Akuna Capital, and Morgan Creek We are moving quickly and have already deployed substantial capital into the space, proving our ability to execute and capture customer demand We offer Competitive salary Unlimited vacation / sick days Employer paid health coverage (vision, dental, 401K) Work alongside an enthusiastic, collegial, and driven team in a highly meritocratic environment Weekly lunch, office snacks and coffee Though we are operating fully remotely while we navigate the current public health climate, this role is will ultimately be located in our downtown Manhattan office. ", 
